HEADWORD: Water lettuce
<hw>Wa"ter let"tuce</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant
(<spn>Pistia stratiotes</spn>) which floats on tropical waters, and
forms a rosette of spongy, wedge-shaped leaves.</def> <rj><au>J. Smith
(Dict. Econ. Plants).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

